  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multi-sector Assistance to Respond to Evolving Needs among Migrant &amp; Host Communities in South-east Turkey in the Context of the COVID-19 Pandemic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support vulnerable populations including Syrian refugees and the Turkish host communities, and to strengthen Turkey&#x2019;s border management system, IOM aims to support a comprehensive protection and capacity building response through the provision of continued support to Ensar Community Centre in Gaziantep through support to establish a Municipal Migrant and Women&#x2019;s Support Centre in Kilis; and the rollout of innovative activities in the Sanliurfa Migrant Information and Coordination Centre.  Additionally, the project will provide an entrepreneurship training program for Syrian refugees and host community members with disabilities in Gaziantep, increase access to basic services through infrastructure rehabilitation, and border management capacity building at Turkey&#x2019;s eastern borders and Istanbul Airport. Overall, IOM aims to target 14,505 beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
